{
  "texts": [
    "However, where there is significant class imbalance, accurate estimation of the 7.",
    "Target class B has been incorrectly mapped to source class L1 in both the M-JDA and BDA results, leading to negative transfer.",
    "underlying marginal distributions is challenging, leading to alignment based on biased estimations.",
    "Thus, this objective may lead to suboptimal mappings.",
    "An alternative solution is to rely on adapting the conditional distributions, as would be the case with BDA where μ ¼ 1, but this increases the risk of negative transfer because of noisy pseudo-labels (Poole et al., 2022)."
  ]
}